  "text": "In order to further assess the relative degree of structural disorder in LBH, we also measured its two-dimensional 1 H- [CITATION_1] N HSQC NMR spectrum (Fig. 3C) . In this analysis, the Thus, pairs of resonances are observed in the upfield regions (Fig. 3C , [CITATION_2] Nd $ 113 ppm and 1 Hd $ 6.9 ppm and $7.7 ppm), as expected for the -NH 2 group in the side chains of the 3 Asn and 4 Gln residues (Fig. 4A, N24 , N94, N100, Q43, Q88, Q92, and Q105). Interestingly, a pair of resonances was observed in the downfield regions (Fig. 3C,   15 Nd = 129 ppm and 1 Hd = 10.1 ppm) for the NeH of the aromatic indole side chain of the single tryptophan (Trp-80), indicating slow exchange between two different conformations. Taken together, our NMR analysis suggests that LBH may not only be structurally disordered but that it may also exhibit conformational flexibility allowing it to exist in multiple conformations.",
